text:
As long as you’re not committing or pushing on the same branch that you pulled then it’ll be fine! You’ll just push your new branch after you’ve made your changes.
```git checkout -b <your-new-branch-name>
'make your changes'
git add .
git commit -m "commit message"
git push origin <your-new-branch-name>```
